Enrichment Analysis

Our Patient Data | Pathway

Mark Edward M. Gonzales1

Dr.Â Anish M.S. Shrestha2

I. Preliminaries

Loading libraries

library("tidyverse")
library("tibble")
library("msigdbr")
library("ggplot2")
library("dplyr")
library("grex")
library("org.Hs.eg.db")
library("clusterProfiler")

II. Gene Ontology Enrichment Analysis

Load the list of differentially expressed genes.

deg <- read.delim("../data/patient/differentially-expressed-genes-untargeted.csv", sep=",")
rownames(deg) <- deg$X
deg$X <- NULL
deg
deg$entrez <- mapIds(
  x = org.Hs.eg.db,
  keys = row.names(deg),
  column = "ENTREZID",
  keytype = "ENSEMBL",
  multiVals = "first"
)
'select()' returned 1:many mapping between keys and columns
deg <- deg[!duplicated(deg$entrez),]
deg <- deg %>% drop_na(entrez)
rownames(deg) <- deg$entrez
deg

Perform pathway enrichment analysis.

genes <- rownames(deg)
enriched <- enrichKEGG(
  gene = genes,
  organism = 'hsa',
  pAdjustMethod = "BH",
  pvalueCutoff = 0.05,
)

as.data.frame(enriched)
plot(barplot(enriched, showCategory = 20))
